@prefix ms: <https://machinespirits.dev/ontology/reasoning#> .
@prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Consistency axioms — the deliberate disjointness set that gives DL
# consistency-checking TEETH over per-role acquired / theory-of-mind ABoxes.
# This module is THEORY-OF-MIND ONLY (decision 2B); structural/casting
# disjointness lives in casting-axioms.ttl and is loaded only by spec validation.
#
# Third module of the shared TBox (reasoning-core ⊕ poetics-core ⊕ consistency),
# same namespace, co-loaded by services/ontology/reasoningOntology.js.
#
# OWL 2 EL-safe (pairwise owl:disjointWith only — no negation/disjunction) so the
# vendored ELK reasoner can use it for proper DL consistency (roadmap step 5). A
# lightweight N3 precursor in consistency-rules.n3 flags violations in the EYE
# pipeline TODAY so the set is demonstrable + testable before ELK is wired.
#
# THE SET DEFINES WHAT COUNTS AS A ToM CONTRADICTION — tune it deliberately.
# Design note: notes/ontology/2026-06-02-unified-ontology-consolidation.md §3.
#
# SNAPSHOT DISCIPLINE (synchronic vs diachronic): disjointness is global in OWL —
# `A disjointWith B` forbids ANY individual from being both, ever. But learning is
# NONMONOTONIC: a learner who moves AuthorityToDeferTo → ThinkingPartner across the
# dialogue is the pedagogical GOAL, not a contradiction. So a point-in-time
# (synchronic) snapshot must be consistent; revision ACROSS snapshots (diachronic)
# is expected development, NOT inconsistency. Consistency is therefore checked over
# one per-turn ABox SNAPSHOT, never the accumulated union — and the cross-turn
# (temporal) layer lives outside the DL. See the design note §3.1.
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

ms:ConsistencyAxioms
  a owl:Ontology ;
  rdfs:label "Machine Spirits ToM / recognition consistency axioms" ;
  rdfs:comment "Deliberate ToM disjointness set for DL consistency-checking of per-role ABoxes. OWL 2 EL-safe; checked per-turn-snapshot, not over the accumulated union." .

# ── Meta-vocabulary (used by consistency-rules.n3 + tooling to report violations) ─
ms:Inconsistent a owl:Class ;
  rdfs:comment "an individual whose asserted/inferred types violate a disjointness axiom" .
ms:violatesDisjointness a owl:ObjectProperty ;
  rdfs:comment "links an inconsistent individual to a class it holds that is disjoint with another it also holds" .

# ── KC-status vocabulary (decision 3A) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Mastery is a property of a LEARNER about a KC, not of the KC in the abstract: the
# ABox mints one status individual per (role's-model-of-learner, KC, turn) and types
# it KCMastered or KCMissing (attachment via ms:aboutLearner / ms:aboutKC). Asserting
# BOTH on that individual (the tutor's model says the learner both has and lacks the
# skill at one snapshot) is the contradiction.
ms:KCStatus a owl:Class .
ms:KCMastered a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf ms:KCStatus .
ms:KCMissing a owl:Class ; rdfs:subClassOf ms:KCStatus .
ms:aboutLearner a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:comment "the learner this KC-status / ToM assertion is about" .
ms:aboutKC a owl:ObjectProperty ; rdfs:range ms:KnowledgeComponent ; rdfs:comment "the knowledge component a KC-status is about" .

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# ToM / recognition contradictions — the load-bearing set (all snapshot-scoped)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# (1) PerceivedRole poles — the recognition axis itself. The learner cannot, at one
#     snapshot, perceive the tutor as BOTH a pure authority-to-defer-to AND a mutual
#     thinking-partner. The whole recognition programme is the defer→partner move.
ms:AuthorityToDeferTo owl:disjointWith ms:ThinkingPartner .

# (2) Claim-ownership poles — a conclusion held as one's own vs held weakly.
ms:ConclusionOwned owl:disjointWith ms:ClaimOwnershipWeak .

# (3A) KC mastery — a learner snapshot cannot both master AND lack the same KC.
#      (The most natural ToM contradiction: a model that says the learner both can
#      and cannot justify their reasoning.)
ms:KCMastered owl:disjointWith ms:KCMissing .

# NOTE: Misrecognition ⊥ RecognitionRepair was CUT (decision 1B). Breakdown→repair
# is a nonmonotonic transition across turns (diachronic), handled by the temporal
# layer, not a synchronic contradiction.
